{{redirect|BKLF|the transcription factor|KLF3}}
'''The Bath Children's Literature Festival''' (also known as Bath Kids' Lit Fest) is an annual book festival held in [[Bath, Somerset]] aimed at children's books. The festival features a variety of authors, poets, illustrators and storytellers. It typically lasts ten days, spanning two weekends. Various events are organised in the city during this time,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bathkidslitfest.co.uk/whats_on.htm |title=Whats On |publisher=Bath Festival of Children's Literature |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090219224555/http://bathkidslitfest.co.uk/whats_on.htm |archivedate=2009-02-19 |df= }}</ref> as well as events at local schools in the central week.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chilton|first1=Martin|title=Bath Children's Literature Festival 2015 lineup|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/books/bath-festival-childrens-literature/lineup/|accessdate=12 February 2017|work=Telegraph|date=24 September 2015}}</ref>

The Festival has been organised by John and Gill McLay since its creation in 2008.

The Festival has attracted a wealth of popular and talented guests, including the [[Children's Laureate]] [[Michael Rosen]], [[Michael Morpurgo]], [[Jacqueline Wilson]], [[Harry Hill]], [[Meg Cabot]] and [[Axel Scheffler]].

